{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775872543098,"sessionID":"ses_285bf99c7ffeh0VXk0ZMqdVuCp","part":{"id":"prt_d7a4082d5001R9sH3ZkihmP3tV","messageID":"msg_d7a4076ed001As5ExauPXv27Tk","sessionID":"ses_285bf99c7ffeh0VXk0ZMqdVuCp","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_28889d71fc78458b884d21d4","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/changes/AR-031/delta-spec.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/changes/AR-031/delta-spec.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # Delta Spec: AR-031 вҖ” RBAC й…ҚзҪ® (SA/Role/Binding)\n2: \n3: ## Overview\n4: \n5: This delta-spec defines acceptance scenarios for implementing RBAC configuration (ServiceAccount, Role, RoleBinding) in the agentcube manifests module.\n6: \n7: ## Base Specifications\n8: \n9: - **AR**: AR-031\n10: - **Module**: `manifests`\n11: - **Language**: YAML\n12: - **Size**: M\n13: \n14: ---\n15: \n16: ## Scenario: ServiceAccount Definitions\n17: \n18: ### AR-031-001: Agent ServiceAccount\n19: \n20: - **GIVEN** Kubernetes namespace for agentcube components\n21: - **WHEN** creating ServiceAccount for agent pods\n22: - **THEN** it SHALL be named `agentcube-agent`\n23: - **AND** SHALL be created in each target namespace\n24: - **AND** SHALL include appropriate imagePullSecrets if needed\n25: \n26: ### AR-031-002: Controller ServiceAccount\n27: \n28: - **GIVEN** namespace for agentcube control plane\n29: - **WHEN** creating ServiceAccount for controllers\n30: - **THEN** it SHALL be named `agentcube-controller`\n31: - **AND** SHALL be created in the agentcube-system namespace\n32: \n33: ---\n34: \n35: ## Scenario: Role Definitions\n36: \n37: ### AR-031-003: Agent Runtime Role\n38: \n39: - **GIVEN** namespace for agent deployment\n40: - **WHEN** defining Role for agent ServiceAccount\n41: - **THEN** it SHALL include permissions for AgentRuntime CRD (get, list, watch)\n42: - **AND** SHALL include permissions for CodeInterpreter CRD (get, list, watch, update, patch)\n43: - **AND** SHALL include permissions forPods (get, list, watch, create, delete)\n44: - **AND** SHALL include permissions for Services (get, list, watch, create, update, delete)\n45: - **AND** SHALL be named `agentcube-agent-runtime`\n46: \n47: ### AR-031-004: Agent Namespace Role\n48: \n49: - **GIVEN** namespace for agent deployment\n50: - **WHEN** defining Role for agent namespace access\n51: - **THEN** it SHALL include permissions for ConfigMaps (get, list, watch, create, update, delete)\n52: - **AND** SHALL include permissions for Secrets (get, list, watch, create, update, delete)\n53: - **AND** SHALL include permissions for Events (get, list, watch, create)\n54: - **AND** SHALL be named `agentcube-agent`\n55: \n56: ### AR-031-005: Controller ClusterRole\n57: \n58: - **GIVEN** cluster-wide scope\n59: - **WHEN** defining ClusterRole for controller\n60: - **THEN** it SHALL include permissions for AgentRuntime CRD (all verbs)\n61: - **AND** SHALL include permissions for CodeInterpreter CRD (all verbs)\n62: - **AND** SHALL include permissions for namespaces (get, list, watch)\n63: - **AND** SHALL include permissions for pods (all verbs)\n64: - **AND** SHALL include permissions for services (all verbs)\n65: - **AND** SHALL include permissions for configmaps (all verbs)\n66: - **AND** SHALL include permissions for secrets (all verbs)\n67: - **AND** SHALL include permissions for events (all verbs)\n68: - **AND** SHALL be named `agentcube-controller`\n69: \n70: ---\n71: \n72: ## Scenario: RoleBinding Definitions\n73: \n74: ### AR-031-006: Agent Runtime RoleBinding\n75: \n76: - **GIVEN** namespace for agent deployment\n77: - **WHEN** creating RoleBinding for agent ServiceAccount\n78: - **THEN** it SHALL bind `agentcube-agent` SA to `agentcube-agent-runtime` Role\n79: - **AND** SHALL be named `agentcube-agent-runtime`\n80: - **AND** SHALL reference correct namespace\n81: \n82: ### AR-031-007: Agent Namespace RoleBinding\n83: \n84: - **GIVEN** namespace for agent deployment\n85: - **WHEN** creating RoleBinding for agent namespace access\n86: - **THEN** it SHALL bind `agentcube-agent` SA to `agentcube-agent` Role\n87: - **AND** SHALL be named `agentcube-agent`\n88: - **AND** SHALL reference correct namespace\n89: \n90: ### AR-031-008: Controller RoleBinding\n91: \n92: - **GIVEN** agentcube-system namespace\n93: - **WHEN** creating RoleBinding for controller\n94: - **THEN** it SHALL bind `agentcube-controller` SA to `agentcube-controller` ClusterRole\n95: - **AND** SHALL be named `agentcube-controller`\n96: - **AND** SHALL use ClusterRoleBinding for cluster-wide access\n97: \n98: ---\n99: \n100: ## Scenario: RBAC Deployment\n101: \n102: ### AR-031-009: RBAC YAML structure\n103: \n104: - **GIVEN** manifests directory\n105: - **WHEN** organizing RBAC YAML files\n106: - **THEN** they SHALL be placed under `manifests/rbac/`\n107: - **AND** SHALL include ServiceAccount YAML files\n108: - **AND** SHALL include Role YAML files\n109: - **AND** SHALL include RoleBinding YAML files\n110: \n111: ### AR-031-010: Namespace isolation\n112: \n113: - **GIVEN** RBAC configuration\n114: - **WHEN** defining roles\n115: - **THEN** Agent roles SHALL be namespace-scoped (Role)\n116: - **AND** Controller roles SHALL be cluster-scoped (ClusterRole)\n117: - **AND** RoleBindings SHALL reference correct namespaces\n118: \n119: ### AR-031-011: Least privilege principle\n120: \n121: - **GIVEN** RBAC configuration\n122: - **WHEN** defining permissions\n123: - **THEN** Agent SA SHALL only have permissions needed for runtime\n124: - **AND** Controller SA SHALL have permissions needed for reconciliation\n125: - **AND** No wildcard (*) permissions SHALL be used unless absolutely necessary\n126: \n127: ---\n128: \n129: ## Scenario: Validation\n130: \n131: ### AR-031-012: YAML syntax validation\n132: \n133: - **GIVEN** RBAC YAML files\n134: - **WHEN** running `kubectl apply --dry-run=client`\n135: - **THEN** all YAMLs SHALL be valid Kubernetes resources\n136: - **AND** SHALL pass schema validation\n137: \n138: ### AR-031-013: RBAC consistency\n139: \n140: - **GIVEN** RBAC configuration\n141: - **WHEN** applying to cluster\n142: - **THEN** ServiceAccounts SHALL exist before RoleBindings reference them\n143: - **AND** Roles SHALL exist before RoleBindings reference them\n144: - **AND** All referenced namespaces SHALL exist\n145: \n146: ---\n147: \n148: ## References\n149: \n150: - Kubernetes RBAC Documentation\n151: - agentcube design: `design.md`\n\n(End of file - total 151 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# Delta Spec: AR-031 вҖ” RBAC й…ҚзҪ® (SA/Role/Binding)\n\n## Overview\n\nThis delta-spec defines acceptance scenarios for implementing RBAC configuration (ServiceAccount, Role, RoleBinding) in the agentcube manifests module.\n\n## Base Specifications\n\n- **AR**: AR-031\n- **Module**: `manifests`\n- **Language**: YAML\n- **Size**: M\n\n---\n\n## Scenario: ServiceAccount Definitions\n\n### AR-031-001: Agent ServiceAccount\n\n- **GIVEN** Kubernetes namespace for agentcube components","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/changes/AR-031/delta-spec.md","time":{"start":1775872543070,"end":1775872543096}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775872543101,"sessionID":"ses_285bf99c7ffeh0VXk0ZMqdVuCp","part":{"id":"prt_d7a408628001bpmLlL8qv1b9SD","messageID":"msg_d7a4076ed001As5ExauPXv27Tk","sessionID":"ses_285bf99c7ffeh0VXk0ZMqdVuCp","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_7a09203b4292406fa3081282","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/changes/AR-030/delta-spec.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/changes/AR-030/delta-spec.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # Delta Spec: AR-030 вҖ” Helm Chart жЁЎжқҝдёҺ Values\n2: \n3: ## Overview\n4: \n5: This delta-spec defines acceptance scenarios for implementing the Helm Chart templates and values configuration for deploying AgentCube to Kubernetes, providing a reusable, configurable deployment mechanism for the Workload Manager, Router, optional Volcano scheduler, and associated RBAC resources.\n6: \n7: ## Base Specifications\n8: \n9: - **AR**: AR-030\n10: - **Module**: `manifests`\n11: - **Language**: YAML\n12: - **Size**: L\n13: - **Base Specs**: `deployment/spec.md`, `deployment/design.md`\n14: \n15: ---\n16: \n17: ## Background\n18: \n19: AgentCube requires a standardized deployment mechanism to Kubernetes clusters. The deployment/spec.md document defines the expected chart structure, but the actual template files need implementation. The Helm chart enables reproducible deployments, configuration management via values.yaml, namespace-scoped installations, optional components (RBAC, Volcano scheduler), and CRD lifecycle management.\n20: \n21: ---\n22: \n23: ## Requirements\n24: \n25: ### AR-030-001: Chart з»“жһ„дёҺе…ғж•°жҚ®\n26: \n27: The Helm chart SHALL provide proper structure and metadata for Helm 3 compatibility.\n28: \n29: #### Scenario: AR-030-001-A вҖ” Chart.yaml еҢ…еҗ«жӯЈзЎ®зҡ„е…ғж•°жҚ®\n30: \n31: - **GIVEN** a chart directory at `manifests/charts/base/`\n32: - **WHEN** `helm lint manifests/charts/base` is executed\n33: - **THEN** it SHALL pass without errors\n34: - **AND** the chart SHALL have `name: agentcube` and `version: 0.1.0` in Chart.yaml\n35: \n36: #### Scenario: AR-030-001-B вҖ” values.yaml еҢ…еҗ«жүҖжңүеҝ…йңҖй…ҚзҪ®йЎ№\n37: \n38: - **GIVEN** the `values.yaml` file exists in the chart\n39: - **WHEN** it is parsed\n40: - **THEN** it SHALL contain keys for `redis.addr`, `redis.password`, `workloadmanager.*`, `router.*`, and `volcano.scheduler.*`\n41: \n42: #### Scenario: AR-030-001-C вҖ” зӣ®еҪ•з»“жһ„е®Ңж•ҙ\n43: \n44: - **GIVEN** the chart directory structure exists\n45: - **WHEN** the chart is inspected\n46: - **THEN** it SHALL contain: `Chart.yaml`, `values.yaml`, `templates/`, and `crds/`\n47: \n48: ---\n49: \n50: ### AR-030-002: Helm е®үиЈ…дёҺ Namespace з®ЎзҗҶ\n51: \n52: The system SHALL support installing/upgrading the AgentCube stack with Helm from `manifests/charts/base`, including namespace creation.\n53: \n54: #### Scenario: AR-030-002-A вҖ” Helm install еҲӣе»ә namespace\n55: \n56: - **GIVEN** a Kubernetes cluster and Helm 3 available\n57: - **AND** `redis.addr` is set to a valid Redis address in values\n58: - **WHEN** `helm upgrade --install agentcube manifests/charts/base --namespace agentcube --create-namespace` is executed\n59: - **THEN** the namespace `agentcube` SHALL be created\n60: - **AND** all resources SHALL be deployed to that namespace\n61: \n62: #### Scenario: AR-030-002-B вҖ” Helm upgrade жҲҗеҠҹжёІжҹ“жЁЎжқҝ\n63: \n64: - **GIVEN** the chart is already installed\n65: - **AND** values are provided with required `redis.addr`\n66: - **WHEN** `helm upgrade agentcube manifests/charts/base --namespace agentcube` runs\n67: - **THEN** it SHALL succeed without manual editing of rendered YAML\n68: \n69: ---\n70: \n71: ### AR-030-003: Redis зҺҜеўғеҸҳйҮҸжіЁе…Ҙ\n72: \n73: The system SHALL require Redis address configuration for Workload Manager and Router at runtime via chart values `redis.addr` and `redis.password`.\n74: \n75: #### Scenario: AR-030-003-A вҖ” Workload Manager жҺҘж”¶ Redis й…ҚзҪ®\n76: \n77: - **GIVEN** `redis.addr: redis-master:6379` and `redis.password: secret123` are set in values\n78: - **WHEN** the Workload Manager pod starts\n79: - **THEN** the container SHALL have `REDIS_ADDR=redis-master:6379` environment variable\n80: - **AND** `REDIS_PASSWORD=secret123` environment variable\n81: \n82: #### Scenario: AR-030-003-B вҖ” Router жҺҘж”¶ Redis й…ҚзҪ®\n83: \n84: - **GIVEN** `redis.addr: redis-master:6379` is set in values\n85: - **WHEN** the Router pod starts\n86: - **THEN** the container SHALL have `REDIS_ADDR=redis-master:6379` environment variable\n87: - **AND** `REDIS_PASSWORD` from values (empty string if not set)\n88: \n89: #### Scenario: AR-030-003-C вҖ” Redis еҜҶз ҒеҸҜдёәз©ә\n90: \n91: - **GIVEN** `redis.addr: redis:6379` is set and `redis.password` is omitted or empty\n92: - **WHEN** pods start\n93: - **THEN** `REDIS_PASSWORD` SHALL be set to empty string `\"\"`\n94: \n95: ---\n96: \n97: ### AR-030-004: Workload Manager Deployment й…ҚзҪ®\n98: \n99: The system SHALL deploy Workload Manager as a `Deployment` and `Service` named `workloadmanager` with configurable replica count, image, service type, resources, health probes, and environment variables.\n100: \n101: #### Scenario: AR-030-004-A вҖ” й»ҳи®ӨеүҜжң¬ж•°\n102: \n103: - **GIVEN** default chart values\n104: - **WHEN** the chart is installed\n105: - **THEN** the Workload Manager `Deployment` SHALL have `replicas: 1`\n106: \n107: #### Scenario: AR-030-004-B вҖ” иҮӘе®ҡд№үеүҜжң¬ж•°\n108: \n109: - **GIVEN** `workloadmanager.replicas: 3` in values\n110: - **WHEN** the chart is rendered\n111: - **THEN** the Deployment SHALL have `replicas: 3`\n112: \n113: #### Scenario: AR-030-004-C вҖ” е®№еҷЁй•ңеғҸеҸҜй…ҚзҪ®\n114: \n115: - **GIVEN** `workloadmanager.image.repository: my-registry/workloadmanager` and `image.tag: v1.0.0` in values\n116: - **WHEN** the Deployment is rendered\n117: - **THEN** the container image SHALL be `my-registry/workloadmanager:v1.0.0`\n118: \n119: #### Scenario: AR-030-004-D вҖ” Service з«ҜеҸЈй…ҚзҪ®\n120: \n121: - **GIVEN** `workloadmanager.service.port: 9090` in values\n122: - **WHEN** the Service is rendered\n123: - **THEN** it SHALL expose port `9090`\n124: - **AND** targetPort SHALL match the container port\n125: \n126: #### Scenario: AR-030-004-E вҖ” еҒҘеә·жЈҖжҹҘжҺўй’Ҳ\n127: \n128: - **GIVEN** default chart values\n129: - **WHEN** the Workload Manager pod is created\n130: - **THEN** it SHALL have a livenessProbe HTTP GET on `/health`\n131: - **AND** a readinessProbe HTTP GET on `/health`\n132: \n133: #### Scenario: AR-030-004-F вҖ” иө„жәҗйҷҗеҲ¶еҸҜй…ҚзҪ®\n134: \n135: - **GIVEN** `workloadmanager.resources.limits.cpu: \"2\"` and `workloadmanager.resources.limits.memory: \"2Gi\"` in values\n136: - **WHEN** the Deployment is rendered\n137: - **THEN** the container SHALL have those resource limits\n138: \n139: #### Scenario: AR-030-004-G вҖ” йўқеӨ–зҺҜеўғеҸҳйҮҸ\n140: \n141: - **GIVEN** `workloadmanager.extraEnv: [{\"name\": \"CUSTOM_VAR\", \"value\": \"custom-value\"}]` in values\n142: - **WHEN** the Deployment is rendered\n143: - **THEN** the container SHALL include `CUSTOM_VAR` environment variable\n144: \n145: ---\n146: \n147: ### AR-030-005: Router Deployment й…ҚзҪ®\n148: \n149: The system SHALL deploy the Router as a `Deployment` and `Service` named `agentcube-router` with replica count, image, ClusterIP service, resources, and `WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL` pointing to the in-cluster Workload Manager service.\n150: \n151: #### Scenario: AR-030-005-A вҖ” Router й»ҳи®ӨеүҜжң¬ж•°\n152: \n153: - **GIVEN** default chart values\n154: - **WHEN** the chart is installed\n155: - **THEN** the Router `Deployment` SHALL have `replicas: 1`\n156: \n157: #### Scenario: AR-030-005-B вҖ” Router иҝһжҺҘеҲ° Workload Manager\n158: \n159: - **GIVEN** release namespace `agentcube` and Workload Manager service port `8080`\n160: - **WHEN** the Router pod starts\n161: - **THEN** it SHALL have `WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL` set to `http://workloadmanager.agentcube.svc.cluster.local:8080`\n162: \n163: #### Scenario: AR-030-005-C вҖ” Router й•ңеғҸеҸҜй…ҚзҪ®\n164: \n165: - **GIVEN** `router.image.repository: my-registry/agentcube-router` and `image.tag: latest` in values\n166: - **WHEN** the Deployment is rendered\n167: - **THEN** the container image SHALL be `my-registry/agentcube-router:latest`\n168: \n169: #### Scenario: AR-030-005-D вҖ” Router Service зұ»еһӢеҸҜй…ҚзҪ®\n170: \n171: - **GIVEN** `router.service.type: LoadBalancer` in values\n172: - **WHEN** the Service is rendered\n173: - **THEN** it SHALL have `type: LoadBalancer`\n174: \n175: #### Scenario: AR-030-005-E вҖ” Router еҒҘеә·жЈҖжҹҘ\n176: \n177: - **GIVEN** default chart values\n178: - **WHEN** the Router pod is created\n179: - **THEN** it SHALL have livenessProbe on `/health/live`\n180: - **AND** readinessProbe on `/health/ready`\n181: \n182: #### Scenario: AR-030-005-F вҖ” Router иө„жәҗйҷҗеҲ¶\n183: \n184: - **GIVEN** `router.resources.limits.cpu: \"1\"` and `router.resources.limits.memory: \"1Gi\"` in values\n185: - **WHEN** the Deployment is rendered\n186: - **THEN** the container SHALL have those resource limits\n187: \n188: #### Scenario: AR-030-005-G вҖ” Router и°ғиҜ•жЁЎејҸ\n189: \n190: - **GIVEN** `router.debug: true` in values\n191: - **WHEN** the Deployment is rendered\n192: - **THEN** the container args SHALL include `--debug`\n193: \n194: ---\n195: \n196: ### AR-030-006: Workload Manager RBAC\n197: \n198: The system SHALL create a `ServiceAccount` `workloadmanager`, a `ClusterRole` `workloadmanager`, and `ClusterRoleBinding` `workloadmanager` granting the required permissions for agent-sandbox, AgentCube runtime CRDs, core workloads, auth, and secrets.\n199: \n200: #### Scenario: AR-030-006-A вҖ” ServiceAccount еҲӣе»ә\n201: \n202: - **GIVEN** chart installation\n203: - **WHEN** RBAC resources are applied\n204: - **THEN** a `ServiceAccount` named `workloadmanager` SHALL be created in the release namespace\n205: \n206: #### Scenario: AR-030-006-B вҖ” ClusterRole жқғйҷҗ\n207: \n208: - **GIVEN** the chart is installed\n209: - **WHEN** the ClusterRole is created\n210: - **THEN** it SHALL include rules for:\n211:   - `sandboxes` (CRD) - all verbs\n212:   - `sandboxclaims` (CRD) - all verbs\n213:   - `codeinterpreters` (CRD) - all verbs\n214:   - `agentruntimes` (CRD) - all verbs\n215:   - `pods` (core) - list, watch, delete\n216:   - `secrets` (core) - get, list, watch, create, update, delete\n217:   - `tokenreviews` (authentication.k8s.io) - create\n218: \n219: #### Scenario: AR-030-006-C вҖ” ClusterRoleBinding з»‘е®ҡ\n220: \n221: - **GIVEN** chart installation in namespace `agentcube`\n222: - **WHEN** RBAC resources are applied\n223: - **THEN** `ClusterRoleBinding/workloadmanager` SHALL bind `ServiceAccount/workloadmanager` in namespace `agentcube` to `ClusterRole/workloadmanager`\n224: \n225: ---\n226: \n227: ### AR-030-007: Router е‘ҪеҗҚз©әй—ҙ RBAC (еҸҜйҖү)\n228: \n229: The system SHALL optionally create namespace-scoped `ServiceAccount`, `Role`, and `RoleBinding` for the Router when `router.rbac.create` is true.\n230: \n231: #### Scenario: AR-030-007-A вҖ” RBAC й»ҳи®ӨзҰҒз”Ё\n232: \n233: - **GIVEN** `router.rbac.create: false` (default)\n234: - **WHEN** templates render\n235: - **THEN** Router optional RBAC manifests SHALL NOT be emitted\n236: \n237: #### Scenario: AR-030-007-B вҖ” RBAC еҗҜз”Ёж—¶еҲӣе»ә\n238: \n239: - **GIVEN** `router.rbac.create: true` in values\n240: - **AND** `router.serviceAccountName: agentcube-router` (or defaulted)\n241: - **WHEN** the chart is applied\n242: - **THEN** a `ServiceAccount` named `agentcube-router` SHALL be created\n243: - **AND** a `Role` granting secrets verbs SHALL be created in the release namespace\n244: - **AND** a `RoleBinding` SHALL bind the ServiceAccount to the Role\n245: \n246: #### Scenario: AR-030-007-C вҖ” Router дҪҝз”Ёдё“з”Ё ServiceAccount\n247: \n248: - **GIVEN** `router.rbac.create: true` and `router.serviceAccountName: custom-router-sa` in values\n249: - **WHEN** the Deployment is rendered\n250: - **THEN** the Router Deployment SHALL use `serviceAccountName: custom-router-sa`\n251: \n252: ---\n253: \n254: ### AR-030-008: Volcano Agent Scheduler (еҸҜйҖү)\n255: \n256: The system SHALL optionally deploy Volcano agent scheduler resources when `volcano.scheduler.enabled` is true.\n257: \n258: #### Scenario: AR-030-008-A вҖ” й»ҳи®ӨдёҚеҗҜз”Ё\n259: \n260: - **GIVEN** `volcano.scheduler.enabled: false` (default)\n261: - **WHEN** templates render\n262: - **THEN** no Volcano scheduler objects SHALL be created\n263: \n264: #### Scenario: AR-030-008-B вҖ” еҗҜз”Ёж—¶еҲӣе»әиө„жәҗ\n265: \n266: - **GIVEN** `volcano.scheduler.enabled: true` in values\n267: - **WHEN** the chart is applied\n268: - **THEN** it SHALL create:\n269:   - `ServiceAccount` for the scheduler\n270:   - `ConfigMap` with agent-scheduler configuration\n271:   - `ClusterRole` with Volcano scheduling permissions\n272:   - `ClusterRoleBinding` for the scheduler\n273:   - `Service` for the scheduler\n274:   - `Deployment` for the scheduler\n275: \n276: #### Scenario: AR-030-008-C вҖ” Volcano й•ңеғҸеҸҜй…ҚзҪ®\n277: \n278: - **GIVEN** `volcano.scheduler.image.repository: custom-volcano/agent-scheduler` in values\n279: - **WHEN** the Deployment is rendered\n280: - **THEN** the container image SHALL use that repository\n281: \n282: ---\n283: \n284: ### AR-030-009: CRD жё…еҚ•\n285: \n286: The system SHALL ship `CustomResourceDefinition` manifests for `agentruntimes` and `codeinterpreters` in the chart's `crds/` directory.\n287: \n288: #### Scenario: AR-030-009-A вҖ” CRD зӣ®еҪ•еӯҳеңЁ\n289: \n290: - **GIVEN** the chart exists\n291: - **WHEN** the chart is inspected\n292: - **THEN** a `crds/` directory SHALL exist with CRD YAML files\n293: \n294: #### Scenario: AR-030-009-B вҖ” AgentRuntime CRD\n295: \n296: - **GIVEN** the CRD manifests are present\n297: - **WHEN** the `agentruntimes` CRD is applied\n298: - **THEN** it SHALL have API group `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh`\n299: - **AND** version `v1alpha1`\n300: - **AND** `scope: Namespaced`\n301: \n302: #### Scenario: AR-030-009-C вҖ” CodeInterpreter CRD\n303: \n304: - **GIVEN** the CRD manifests are present\n305: - **WHEN** the `codeinterpreters` CRD is applied\n306: - **THEN** it SHALL have API group `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh`\n307: - **AND** version `v1alpha1`\n308: - **AND** `scope: Namespaced`\n309: \n310: ---\n311: \n312: ### AR-030-010: Helm жЁЎжқҝйӘҢиҜҒ\n313: \n314: The chart SHALL pass Helm validation and render correctly.\n315: \n316: #### Scenario: AR-030-010-A вҖ” Helm lint йҖҡиҝҮ\n317: \n318: - **GIVEN** the chart at `manifests/charts/base/`\n319: - **WHEN** `helm lint manifests/charts/base` is executed\n320: - **THEN** it SHALL exit with code 0 (success)\n321: \n322: #### Scenario: AR-030-010-B вҖ” жЁЎжқҝжёІжҹ“ж— й”ҷиҜҜ\n323: \n324: - **GIVEN** `redis.addr: redis:6379` is provided\n325: - **WHEN** `helm template test manifests/charts/base` runs\n326: - **THEN** it SHALL render without errors\n327: - **AND** produce valid Kubernetes YAML\n328: \n329: #### Scenario: AR-030-010-C вҖ” е®Ңж•ҙжёІжҹ“еҢ…еҗ«жүҖжңүиө„жәҗ\n330: \n331: - **GIVEN** all required values are provided\n332: - **AND** `router.rbac.create: true` and `volcano.scheduler.enabled: true`\n333: - **WHEN** the chart is rendered\n334: - **THEN** output SHALL include:\n335:   - WorkloadManager Deployment and Service\n336:   - Router Deployment and Service\n337:   - WorkloadManager RBAC (ServiceAccount, ClusterRole, ClusterRoleBinding)\n338:   - Router RBAC (ServiceAccount, Role, RoleBinding)\n339:   - Volcano scheduler resources\n340:   - CRDs installed via `crds/` directory\n341: \n342: ---\n343: \n344: ## Non-Requirements\n345: \n346: The following are explicitly out of scope for this AR:\n347: \n348: - Kubernetes cluster provisioning\n349: - Ingress configuration\n350: - Prometheus/Grafana monitoring stack\n351: - Redis deployment (external dependency)\n352: - Application-level secrets management beyond RBAC\n353: - Multi-cluster deployment strategies\n354: - Helm hook-based upgrade migrations\n355: - Custom Ingress or NetworkPolicy configurations\n356: \n357: ---\n358: \n359: ## Dependencies\n360: \n361: | Dependency | Description |\n362: |------------|-------------|\n363: | deployment/spec.md | Base deployment requirements |\n364: | deployment/design.md | Helm chart specification |\n365: | pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/ | CRD type definitions (source for generated CRDs) |\n366: | Helm 3 | Chart rendering and installation |\n367: | Kubernetes 1.19+ | API versions used |\n368: \n369: ---\n370: \n371: ## Acceptance Criteria\n372: \n373: | ID | Criterion | Verification Method |\n374: |----|-----------|---------------------|\n375: | AC030-001 | Chart.yaml renders with name=agentcube, version=0.1.0 | `helm lint` |\n376: | AC030-002 | values.yaml contains all documented keys with correct defaults | YAML parsing |\n377: | AC030-003 | Helm install creates namespace | `kubectl get ns` |\n378: | AC030-004 | Workload Manager receives REDIS_ADDR and REDIS_PASSWORD env vars | Pod inspection |\n379: | AC030-005 | Router receives REDIS_ADDR and REDIS_PASSWORD env vars | Pod inspection |\n380: | AC030-006 | Workload Manager Deployment has configurable replicas | `helm template` inspection |\n381: | AC030-007 | Workload Manager Service exposes correct port | Service YAML inspection |\n382: | AC030-008 | Router has WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL pointing to Workload Manager | Pod env inspection |\n383: | AC030-009 | RBAC ClusterRole contains required permissions | ClusterRole YAML inspection |\n384: | AC030-010 | Optional router RBAC renders only when enabled | Conditional rendering test |\n385: | AC030-011 | Optional Volcano scheduler renders only when enabled | Conditional rendering test |\n386: | AC030-012 | CRDs present in crds/ directory | Directory inspection |\n387: | AC030-013 | Helm template renders without error | `helm template` exit code |\n388: | AC030-014 | Helm lint passes | `helm lint` exit code |\n389: \n390: ---\n391: \n392: ## Test Strategy\n393: \n394: ### Unit Tests\n395: - Validate Chart.yaml and values.yaml structure\n396: - Test conditional rendering logic in templates\n397: - Verify RBAC rule completeness\n398: - Verify environment variable injection\n399: \n400: ### Integration Tests\n401: - Test `helm install` and `helm upgrade` in a kind cluster\n402: - Verify all resources are created correctly\n403: - Test optional component toggles\n404: - Validate RBAC bindings\n405: \n406: ### Template Validation\n407: - Use `helm template` for rendering tests\n408: - Use `helm lint` for schema validation\n409: - Use `helm diff` for upgrade path testing\n\n(End of file - total 409 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# Delta Spec: AR-030 вҖ” Helm Chart жЁЎжқҝдёҺ Values\n\n## Overview\n\nThis delta-spec defines acceptance scenarios for implementing the Helm Chart templates and values configuration for deploying AgentCube to Kubernetes, providing a reusable, configurable deployment mechanism for the Workload Manager, Router, optional Volcano scheduler, and associated RBAC resources.\n\n## Base Specifications\n\n- **AR**: AR-030\n- **Module**: `manifests`\n- **Language**: YAML\n- **Size**: L\n- **Base Specs**: `deployment/spec.md`, `deployment/design.md`\n\n---\n\n## Background\n\nAgentCube requires a standardized deployment mechanism to Kubernetes clusters. The deployment/spec.md document defines the expected chart structure, but the actual template files need implementation. The Helm chart enables reproducible deployments, configuration management via values.yaml, namespace-scoped installations, optional components (RBAC, Volcano scheduler), and CRD lifecycle management.\n","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/changes/AR-030/delta-spec.md","time":{"start":1775872543074,"end":1775872543098}}}}
